3.3 Mandatory Safety Rules
You agree at all times to follow universally recognized firearm safety rules, including:
Treat every firearm as if it is loaded.
Never point a firearm at anything you are not willing to destroy.
Keep your finger off the trigger until your sights are on the target and you have decided to fire.
Be certain of your target and what is beyond it.
Before any dry-fire practice, completely unload the firearm; physically and visually inspect the chamber and magazine well; remove all live ammunition from the practice area and from the same room; and use a safe, designated backstop oriented in a safe direction.
Never mix live ammunition with dry-fire practice. Never load a firearm in a dry-fire practice area. Always re-confirm the firearm is unloaded after any interruption.
Wear appropriate eye protection during dry-fire practice when using any tool, slide-racking device, magazine, holster, or accessory.
Comply with all federal, state, and local laws governing the possession, transportation, storage, and use of firearms and ammunition.
3.4 No Substitute for Qualified Instruction
The App, including any drills, articles, videos, or training content delivered through it, is provided for general informational and practice-support purposes only. The App is not a substitute for hands-on instruction by a qualified, certified firearms instructor, for medical or psychological evaluation, or for legal advice regarding the use of force. You should not undertake any technique, drill, or activity described in the App without first obtaining appropriate qualified instruction and confirming that the activity is appropriate and lawful for you.
3.5 Health, Fitness, and Medical Disclaimer
Firearms training and dry-fire practice can involve physical exertion, repetitive motion, sudden movement, and stress. Consult a qualified physician before beginning any training program if you have any medical condition, injury, pregnancy, cardiovascular condition, or other concern. If you experience pain, dizziness, shortness of breath, chest discomfort, or any other adverse symptom while using the App, stop immediately and seek medical attention.
3.6 Audible Cues, Timers, and Vibration
